Posts.Content: kyle wrote: i haven't been here in awhile. i have been cancer free for 3 and a half yrs. and thought it was all behind me. i found a lump under my arm today. it is sore. opposite side from my first breast lump. we moved to maine last summer from ct. i have no dr. here since i haven't had a need. my husband has just been told he has to look for a new job. which means we will be moving to another state this summer. i am frozen with fear. i don't not know what the first step to take is.do you think it is cancer? again?
